Irked by the presence of Moses Kuria at a Building Bridges Initiative rally in Kitui last February, Ngilu took to the microphone and ordered immediate ejection of the Member of Parliament for Gatundu South.Governors can pillage public resources with utter impunity but remain secure in their position. Kennedy Chesoli: Kenyans opposed to the intolerance, fraud perpetuated through the BBI

Winds of change, signalling a political reawakening, are blowing across the land and Ukambani is the epicentre for this phenomenon. In the past few months, Charity Ngilu and Kalonzo Musyoka — individuals that seek to dominate Ukambani politics — have been publicly humiliated.



