Irked by the presence of Moses Kuria at a Building Bridges Initiative rally in Kitui last February, Ngilu took to the microphone and ordered immediate ejection of the Member of Parliament for Gatundu South. Ngilu was simply setting the stage for the agenda of the day — insolent attacks on the Deputy President and his allies — something that had become the mainstay of those Raila Odinga-led rallies.
Instead of a thunderous roar of approval, Ngilu was booed and heckled. The Kitui governor had gone too far and her own people were there to remind her that she was misusing her power and office.





 They demanded that Kuria gets seated among the day’s dignitaries where he truly belonged. This singular act of defiance and civil disobedience would come to define that infamous rally. Madam Ngilu is a brilliant politician, yet BBI seems to have clouded her judgment and she is not alone.
Corrupt officials
Nearly all politicians that have pledged blind support to President Kenyatta and Mr Odinga to amend the Constitution, whichever way they see fit, regard themselves as new owners of the Republic. They are untouchable; for one of them even shot someone in a club, on camera, and continued to puff on his cigar.



