Despite repeated pleas for audience, Mr Musyoka embarrassingly read hollow platitudes to empty chairs. These events exemplify ways in which Kenyans are expressing disgust to the stream of nonsense, intolerance, and fraud perpetuated through the BBI. It’s instructive that people are finally taking a stand against these chest-thumping fellas with inflated egos. They are making it clear that they would no longer accept to be corralled and steered like passive sheep to the slaughterhouse.





Unwarranted scorn
The President seems to relish public humiliation of his deputy and has not reprimanded members of his government, including his Cabinet secretaries that continue to undermine the office of the Deputy President.
At one of the BBI events, the man was visibly delighted and giddy as the likes of Junet Mohamed mocked and humiliated the DP. Whereas the DP has remained largely unmoved, he continues to attract unwarranted scorn from a long list of individuals, including the Secretary-General of Cotu Francis Atwoli, Mombasa Governor Hassan Ali Joho and the Chairman of the Kenya Human Rights Commission.
BBI proponents may mock the DP or force Kenyans to swallow their bitter pill, but that would still not make it right or palpable. Ms Ngilu and Mr Musyoka must explain to the residents of Lower Eastern how expanding the Executive and jerking up taxes would transform lives.



