In Western Kenya, Musalia Mudavadi and other supremos should not merely get Luhyas to endorse a document that has no real benefits to them. They should first explain why they have allowed this government to undermine the sugar sector which supported their community. This is people-centric discussion that is more important than ever, given Covid-inspired challenges.
 kenchesoli@gmail.com Jubilee and OMD have submitted names to the IEBC amid talks of cooperation. Impeached Waititu and exiled Miguna are also in the contest. They have joined nurses and clinicians in their strike, a decision that will further paralyse services in public hospitals. A six-tonne consignment of drugs wasted away at the airport for three years because government officials differed over its clearance.